> Primary Architectural Reference â€” Single Source of Truth

This document defines the architectural principles, decisions, transitional strategies, and long-term vision for this system. All implementation must comply with this document unless an explicit ADR (Architectural Decision Record) states otherwise.




---

ðŸŽ¯ Architectural North Star

We are not building pages. We are building a system that must live, evolve, and scale.

This architecture prioritizes:

Longevity over speed

Explicit decisions over implicit hacks

Modular growth over monolithic convenience

Architectural governance over ad-hoc fixes



---

ðŸ§  Core Architectural Principles

1. Zero-Intelligence Router

> The Router must contain no logic, no data, no conditions, no props.



Router responsibilities:

Route declaration only

Component wiring only


âŒ Router must NOT:

Fetch data

Pass props

Contain business logic

Make architectural decisions



---

2. Self-Contained Pages

Every page must be self-contained.

A page:

Owns its data access

Owns its state

Owns its side-effects


âŒ A page must NOT:

Receive business data via props from Router

Depend on parent for core data



---

3. Explicit Transitional Architecture

Temporary solutions are allowed only if:

They are documented

They are tracked as Technical Debt

They have a Sunset Clause

They align with long-term architecture


âŒ Silent hacks are forbidden âŒ Implicit debt is forbidden


---

4. Feature-Based Architecture (Target)

Long-term structure is Feature Modules, not Pages.

We do NOT scale by files. We scale by bounded contexts and features.


---

ðŸ§© Current Transitional State

Projects Page

Status: Transitional / Architecturally Acknowledged Debt

Current issues:

God Component (700+ lines)

Mixed layers (UI + Data + Business Logic)

Embedded features (comments, gallery, assets)


This is intentional and documented during transition.


---

ADR-001 â€” Transitional useProjects Hook

Status

ACCEPTED


---

Context

Projects page is a God Component

It previously received data via Router props

This violated Self-Contained principle



---

Decision

Introduce a transitional useProjects hook to:

Make Projects page self-contained

Clean Router

Preserve business continuity


This hook is NOT final architecture.


---

Rationale

Why this approach:

Enables immediate Router compliance

Avoids blocking other work

Creates architectural breathing room

Preserves architectural narrative


Rejected alternatives:

Full rewrite now âŒ

Keeping props âŒ

Silent temporary fix âŒ



---

Consequences

Positive:

Router becomes Zero-Intelligence

Page becomes Self-Contained

Architectural governance preserved


Negative (Managed):

God Component remains temporarily

Transitional hook added

Requires scheduled refactor



---

Sunset Clause

This transitional hook must be removed by Q3 2024 and replaced with:

Feature-based modules

Clean data layer

Proper domain separation



---

Architectural Debt Register

PRJ-001 â€” Projects Page God Component

Component: Projects.tsx

Type: Architectural

Severity: High

Introduced: Transitional Phase

Target Resolution: Q3 2024


Technical Description:

700+ lines

UI + Business Logic + Data Access mixed

Embedded Comments, Gallery, Assets

Firebase access at component level


Business Impact if Unresolved:

High maintenance cost

Difficult parallel development

High onboarding time

Increased bug surface



