    â””â”€â”€ types/      # Domain types

Benefits:

Parallel team development

Clear ownership

Scalable complexity

Testable features

Reduced cognitive load



---

Migration Strategy

We follow Strangler Pattern:

1. Build new features alongside old


2. Gradually extract responsibilities


3. Run systems in parallel


4. Cut over when stable



No big-bang rewrites.


---

Governance Rules

What is allowed:

Transitional hooks (documented)

Temporary architecture (with sunset)

Explicit debt


What is forbidden:

Silent hacks

Router logic

Props as data layer

Undocumented architectural changes



---

Team Operating Model

We operate as System Architects, not task solvers.

We prioritize:

Architectural clarity

Long-term maintainability

Decision documentation

System longevity



---

Execution Policy

Once an ADR is:

Accepted

Documented


âž¡ï¸ It is executed.

No architectural second-guessing without new ADR.


